caption: We went there for the first time tonight with my family. We were so impressed with our waitress. We explained that it was our first time there and she helped us pick out the most amazing meal. The waitress was kind, patient, and so sweet. The food was amazing and we all came home raving about it. This is our favorite Korean BBQ. Bravo!!

My husband and I stopped by after a gym workout since I wanted to get something for dinner. First and foremost, the inside looks really really amazing. I've been eyeing this place for a while and wanting to try it. We ended up getting appetizers to go. We got the Soy Garlic chicken, Kimchi fries and the Bulgogi nachos. Everything.Was.AMAZING.  The kimchi fries had so much flavor. The bulgogi was fantastic and well seasoned!  It was delicious. We do want to go back and eventually try more.
Galbi was made perfectly. Great service and full bar service as well. Can’t go wrong here.

Ordered from here 3 times so far and the first time was amazing but the second time wasn't as great and the last time was pretty bad.  The first time we had a variety of things like the kimchi fries, wings, galbitang and pork belly which were all delicious! The second time we got the wings and galbitang. And the last time we got the wings and the jjampong.  The wings progressively got worse for some reason. Maybe it was the delivery or different chefs, idk. But the jjampong for some reason the soup and the noodles came together in the same container so by the time it got to me, there was barely any soup left and the noodles were mad soggy. Plus, there wasn't much flavor to the jjampong as I was expecting. Maybe it's to cater to those who can't handle spiciness or something, but it was more than that -- there was a lack of depth to it overall.  Get the wings and kimchi fries! Don't get the jjampong.

I like to go with friends to this restaurant with my warmest recommendations. I  go to this restaurant often. This recommendation is always successful. The dishes they serve are appetizing and the stuff is generous and cooperative. Every time  we visit this place we enjoy a gorgeous time.  highly recommended.
Awesome vibes and super personal service. The food was crisp and delightful. Will easily recommend this restaurant to others. Convenient prices and generous meals. Great job.
Was a bit skeptical to try at first but I went through with it and it ended up being extremely hood. The guy was hilarious and made the experience 100 times better. I would recommend going here
It was well spaced, nice ambient lighting and service was friendly and prompt
Very well organised and welcoming place. They serve generous portions and for economical prices. We liked the menu a lot and the staff were super friendly and explanatory. Highly recommended.

Came here to try the famous Galbi Jjim. Our first night in NB we passed by Ssam Korean Bistro and the line up was insane! Came back Monday night around 9 hoping it was better and indeed it was. We ordered the Galbi Jjim with brown rice and it was absolutely delicious!! Like everyone says this is a definite must try in NB. We got regular spicy and it was perfect.

I celebrated my graduation this evening in this fine place. I am glad to say that we enjoyed a enjoyable evening and the place was absolutely one of the reasons for this happy gathering. The stuff  collaborated in a gorgeous style, the food was yummy and my buddies were very  joyful. We shall surely visit again for more joyful events. thanks very much.

They got my order pretty wrong. Just came back from picking up my vegetarian ramen order and it had meat in it. The receipt on it had everything right. I don't know how you can mess up that badly. I can't go back to the place since I live 30 min away by train. And now I don't have dinner.

Reviewing again... I’m posting a $16 seafood jiamppong ramen...or is it an upgraded nongshim instant noodle? The noodle is bad even in instant noodle standard, it’s over cooked. Ive dine in here few times before pandemic and it was bad then, I got staled veggie once and their foods are mediocre the rest of time, not worth the price at all. I wanted to give it a try this time, but still… not comparing to fort Lee k food or K town food, just talking about this neighborhood, you always have better choices…

This is not a Korean restaurant. We ordered cold noodle but instead of buckwheat noodle, we got just yam potato noodle in a terrible mirin soup. They didn't even have mustard and rice vinegar. Terrible taste (tasteless)
I had a superb experience in this place. We liked the amazing ambience and the menu. The staff were very personal. I’m glad we ultimately decided to visit this spot.
I certainly loved the food and service, great location very close to my house. The staff members are always kind. I highly recommend this place.
(Translated by Google) Excellent attention (Dany) very good service and DIVINE food! worth it!  (Original) Excelente atención (Dany) muy buen servicio y la comida DIVINA! vale la pena!
Amazing place. Great food, great sake, excellent service. A true gem! I highly recommend if you're in the mood for Korean

Ordered the salmon avocado stone bowl today. The salmon was raw in the middle, not cooked thoroughly AT ALL.  Called to tell them so I can get another one delivered to me and they proceeded to tell me that they had no delivery person and it was through Seamless and I can pick it up.  That is 100% unacceptable!!! I paid $16.00 for that food, only to get told I can only receive a refund.  Guess it’s for the best. I’m not trying to get food poisoning!!
Tried this spot already with a friend and I am obsessed since then. I liked the awesome atmosphere and flavorful dishes and beverages. 5 stars from me.

(Translated by Google) Pleasant restaurant, authentic and very quiet. I was served 1 meal which can be eaten by three people. As a Vegetarian, 1⃣ vegetable meal. With their authentic glasses. This is a 1st special restaurant. Merit 5 *  (Original) Agréable restaurant, authentique et très calme. J'ai été servi 1⃣ repas qui peut être consommer par trois personnes. En tant Vegetarian, 1⃣ repas vegetable. Avec leurs verres authentique. C'est un 1⃣ restaurant spécial. Mérite 5*
This restaurant has wonderful service as well as tasty meals. The best spot in town. The drinks and food came out rapidly and the prices are reasonable. Recommended.
One of my go-to spots to eat. very good location, clean, and good service. I recommend this place!
Genuine food and Great Staff!
Delicious and memorable
Did not enjoy my experience whatsoever. With my yellow rice and watery food, please do yourself a favor and enjoy authentic food in queens instead.

We met with friends at this spot for lunch. we heard about this place from quite a few people.  Well, it was a winning. we were warmly welcomed by the crew  and we felt fantastic. The food was just great. We loved this spot very much and we will visit this place again. we highly recommend this place.

I go to this outstanding place every couple of days since I like the  special atmosphere that is outline this restaurant. The team is awfuly cordial and experienced. The service is extremely rapid. Also, the food they cook is outstanding. I frequent many times and I was always joyful. The pay is fair. I suggest this restaurant to my friends and family.
Good food decent price

I arrive at this special place often because I like the ambiance that is part of this restaurant. The team is highly loving and professional. The service is awfully quick. Also, the food they serve is first-rate. I frequent often and I was always happy. The price is decent. I recommend this place to to all.
Would certainly recommend trying this spot. Excellent ambience, delicious dishes, fantastic customer service. 5 stars.
Had a fantastic experience here with my friend. The food arrives quick and the service is just excellent. Prices are fair.
Tastes like a lie. Never again. Ahjumma would be disappointed.
We have ordered twice for delivery, both times the food came quickly and hot! The food was fresh and tasty, would definitely order again. Gave 4 stars because I haven’t been to the restaurant to eat.

The decor and ambience is great, but the food is quite mediocre. I had the bulgogi: it was too sweet. The pork belly tapas was great, though. My friend had the vegetarian option with tofu and kale. She said it had no flavor and just had a smoky flavor. I had a morsel of her tofu: it indeed only tasted like the charred aftermath of a California wildfire. They had no potatoes so we could neither order the kimchi fries not the truffle fries. I ordered a $4 homemade limeade only to receive simply syrup, seltzer water, and a 1/4 slice of lime. Our attending staff didn’t pay any attention to us at all and showed up only three times during the entire meal: to take the order, serve the order, and take the check. A thoroughly disappointing experience. 2.5 stars.

I found my new go to place!!! The lighting, music, drinks and food was amazing but what made it a place I will continue to visit is the bartender, David! He has such great energy and conversation was something divine. I'm glad I visit Saam Korean bistro not once but twice in one day!! I'll be back soon.

Popped in for lunch as the rain started and we couldn't thank Mother Nature more. Fantastic kimchi rice with spicy pork (juyuk?). Incredibly savory with just enough kick to make each bite interesting. Our server was extremely nice and even brought out a sample of wings when I asked about them. Definitely going back.
Best korean around
Really good service and food! The staff was nice and the food came quick. I have both ordered from for takeout and eaten in the restaurant both instances were good and I will definitely be back!
Mad cozy, little town village feeling
Had to have my Kimchee Fried Ri e & a Soju.  Life is good!.

(Translated by Google) Korean food shop that you can feel free to put in. Rather than being a full-fledged Korean restaurant, it feels like a set-menu that can be used for lunch and dinner for a while. The price was reasonable, and the amount was delicious.  (Original) 気軽に入れる韓国料理のお店。 本格的な韓国料理屋さんと言うより、ちょっとお昼や夕食に使える定食屋さんという感じ。 お値段も手頃で、量も充分、美味しかったです。
Awesome food! Great quality. Tad pricey but not unusual for the area. Our table had 4 dudes and we paid 140. With 3 apps.

Stopped in on a cold rainy day wanting a hot soup, off hour not too busy. Ordered the short rib soup, which was flavorless — no salt, spice, anything. And besides that, the short rib was all gristle. The bartender noticed after I had dumped salt and hot sauce on each bite. Ordered the salmon stone pop — also bland. So disappointing. I thought the bartender was nice and attentive but he left the soup sitting there the whole time and charged me for the more expensive dish (the salmon). Whatever, never going back, there are so many yummy Korean spots for less.

Totally opposite from what I read from google review. Staffs were not friendly at all.Foods are quality wise nice but taste wise not authentic at all. If you are Korean craving for authentic Korean  you will be very disappointed. However if you are non Korean looking for something different this could be one of the good options. Because when I go for Italian or French how am I gonna know if one is authentic or not.I might fall in love with some Italian or French which are not authentic at all. I get to somewhat agree with Brian Kim's opinion below when I scroll down the google review. I am having trouble to digest the food I had here tonight It has been couple of hours but still I am not sure if it is because of the food or treatment I get there I need some alka seltzer

We had a great dinner here recently and it was our first time. The servers were very good, friendly, and accommodating to our questions about the dishes they had. - it feels like we are there long-time customers. Their meats were superb with super fresh, tender meat and amazing sauce. It was absolutely delicious, and everyone enjoyed it. Overall, a good experience. Will definitely return if given an opportunity.

Good quality food. Menu is a bit small but what they do, they do well. Service was a tad slow but its New Years day so I'll chock it up to a slow business day for now.  The Lemon Soju is actually very different and havent seen that anywhere else
(Translated by Google) They have such cool soups that you will 👍🏻  (Original) ისეთი მაგარი სუპები აქვთ, გამოგაყლევებთ 👍🏻
Wouldn't order kimchi fries again. Dolsot bibimbap was alright

Takes waaaaaay to long to come out. And the pho looks like they open a package of those .50 cent ramens and dumped it into a greasy bowl of broth (which had no flavor and was just loaded with oil spots.) And at that price point, this place will not hey my business ever again.
Fantastic food !
Placed a to go order of one thing earlier. Waited about 45 minutes And never got our food. We left and went somewhere else
Delicious ramen, service a little slow, and i was expecting more Korean appetizers. But generally nice place to eat in
This spot clearly knows how to take care of their clients. Always with a very nice attitude. The food is affordably priced, always tasty and neat.

Budae Jiggae, kimchi dumplings, everything here was so good and authentic Korean food. The kimchi was really flavorful and really well aged. My husband, who is from Seoul, felt really at home in here. Service may be a little slow so if you want a fast meal don’t come but we thought it was the perfect pace for an intimate dinner and drinks. Will be back again for sure!
I really enjoy their dishes. I always get excellent customer service there. The place is well organised and the cashiers are always welcoming. I highly recommend this place.
This spot is worth visiting. They have large portions for fair prices. Always clean and with awesome ambience. I highly recommend this place.
Large portions. Great taste.

We met with friends at this restaurant for a meeting. we heard about this restaurant from many people.  Well, it was very nice. The crew were extremely nice and we had a great feeling. The meal was great. We loved this restaurant a lot and we will definitely return to this restaurant. Warmly recommended.
Good place to eat.

Quality has been going down for a while. It feel like the place has changed hands a few times in the past several years. Now the seafood was overcooked and bland, and the beef dumplings empty and soaked in oil. No reason for me to go back.
One of my main places to eat. great location, clean, and awesome service. Very good job!

Surprisingly great find! Walking down Smith St. looking for a new place to eat and was happy to stumble upon this place. Walking in felt like a hole in the wall join, but in a extremely good way. This place had a very modern, rustic design with the right food accompanying it. The service was excellent and the food was too notch. Highly recommend!

The service here is PAINFULLY SLOW. It doesn’t seem to be the servers’ fault—they’re nice—but the place is seriously understaffed. When the bartender is the only staff in sight for a very long time, you know the manager is cutting corners. More than once, I’ve waited more than 20 MINUTES just to get the check. It’s like once they give you your food, they completely forget about you. I kept coming back because the food is good, but boy do they make it hard.

This place is literally a block and a half away from me and I haven't tried much but the one time I went the Truffle fries stood out to me. I've had truffle fries before and I don't like all truffle fries. You would expect a truffle fries would be delicious without a doubt but that is not true. everything else I was really good also
This spot is one of my favorites! Fair pricing, large dishes and the employees are always nice.
This place is worth visiting. They serve big portions for reasonable prices. Constantly well organized and with good atmosphere. I highly recommend this place.

Don't bother ordering from here on seamless.  Your food will NEVER show up or be delivered cold and incorrect.  Because of seamless I have a bad taste in my mouth for this restaurant, they should not do business with seamless as it is an awful company that is tarnishing their reputation beyond incorrect orders.

I was nearby, so I came for the lunch special. Ordered the kimchi fried rice with bulgogi and the wing platter and chose the soy garlic flavor (6 piece with fries, salad, rice and a runny egg). Service was great, seated and food came by fairly quick. The only downside would be that the kimchi fried rice was too salty and it was hard to eat a couple bites without eating it with something else to balance out the flavor.
I tried this place already with a friend and I am obsessed since then. I liked the good mood and delightful dishes and beverages. They never disappoint.
The customer service is regularly fast, lovely vibes, helpful staff members. I will visit here again when I get in town.
This place sure knows how to serve their customers. Constantly with a very welcoming attitude. The food is fairly priced, constantly delightful and clean.
Excellent Korean Food! The decor reminded me of my days when I lived out in Korea. It is authentic as it gets here folks. They have a nice lunch special.
Had a great rib eye bibimbap on a burning hot stone bowl, which yielded fantastic crispy rice. And friendly staff.

Food was indeed incredible but this place gets 5 stars also because of their service. There were even free appetizers that was "refilled" when we finished it. The servers as well we're on their business. I spoke with a male server there, don't remember his name but he was awesome.

Great flavors and options, definitely consider the lunch specials. I ordered the spicy soba with broiled salmon, and it was really good. They even made the dish less spicy and gave kimchi on the side. Definitely try this place out, don't even travel to the city.
The food was very bland.
Great lunch specials. Recommended: Steak and eggs. Steak was marinated perfectly.
Good food and ambience. Dishes are on point and surprisingly, they had a couple of side dishes.

The cook here is not consistent. Sometimes it's good, and sometimes it's just horrible - unendibly bad. It's disgusting. The kimchi fermentation is just not consistent too. For today, the kimchi has gone bad. It's beyond sour. I had budaejjigae for once, it tasted disgusting. It litereally tasted like a vomit. So I tried to kimchi itself, and you can definitely tell the kimchi has gone bad. It tastes like they turned off the kimchi fridge or something for long time. It was disgusting. I am Korean Asian myself, and I know what kimchi tastes like. For O-Sam, they don't stir-fry squid and pork together. So the squid doesn't have any sauce inside or cooked. For kimchi pork and tofu, since the kimchi has gone bad.. you can imagine how it tasted. DON'T EAT HERE. I won't come back here even if the food is free. I'd rather have a cheap cup noddle since at least it's not disgusting.
Good Korean food. Friendly service.
Good Korean Chicken wings and dukbokki!
Wonderful atmosphere. Lovely people. The food is appetizing.
Very nice and quite place to eat.
Love it The fusion of Korean and some American foods this place offers are great.
Service could be a little more attentive for the price but the space is really nice and the tunes are happenin...  Good food. Clean place.

I'm generally not a massive Korean food fan so I'm excited when I find a place that I really like. Attaboy in NYC is definitely amazing, and Ssam in Brooklyn is worth your time as well. The menu is fairly extensive and offers a lot of diversity for your plate. I like that they start you right off with some nicely spiced kimchi. I've had the Galbitang (beef short rib soup), the beef Bulgogi hot pot, the salmon avocado stone bowl (a lunch time offering), and the vege dumplings. Everything here has been good. There are not a lot of Korean food offerings in the Brooklyn Heights/Cobble Hill/Carroll Gardens area so if you need your fix - head to Ssam.
One of the best Korean restaurants in Brooklyn! I visit here every month whenever I want Korean food. Don't need to travel all the way to Koreatown in Manhattan.
Their Honghap Tang is really good. If you don't like spicy food, and want something special that you can't usually get from other Korean restaurants, I recommend to go with this soup!
The rib beef soup was fantastic. Prompt and cordial service.

Great lunch. We had bulgogi, beef dumplings, and kale salad. No clue on the drinks, but, they have a decent cocktail list and decent sized bar.  The staff were lacking. They forgot some of our food. They brought the wrong check. Then they attempted to charge us for the forgotten food. They seemed new. Given the mostly empty restaurant that seems plausible.  The interior was comfortable, but the table was sticky. It wasn’t too bad, just kinda annoying.  Even given my complaining, we’ll be back. It was good food, in a good spot, and has a comfortable/calm environment.
Excellent Korean cuisine, great vibe.

I visited my friends in Brooklyn, and we decided to get lunch with Korean foods here because it was close. And we loved it. They have all sorts of bibimbap served with hot stone pot. I ordered one with Eel, and loved it!
They have authentic bibimbaps, I would say it's one of the best places in NYC. Salmon, Eel, and Kale & Tufu are something that you won't be able to find in any other Korean restaurants
I'm so happy that this Korean BBQ place is right near my house! Their price is better than ones in Manhattan, but quality is very good. Pretty amazed!
I and my friends love Korean ramens. And they have special spicy noodle called Jjamppong ramen. It comes with seafood, and taste is really really good!
Best Korean restaurant in Brooklyn!!
Beyond the expectations, pretty impressed!
Good food and drinks
Reasonable price, top quality food.
Love their happy hour~
Food was pretty good a bit salty for my taste.I had an old fashioned their and it wasn't made correctly.
Go ahead, you can drool 🤤 Food was decent and their French fries should not even be in their menu, just saying! It tasted like frozen ff, had no taste to it.
Great happy hour!

This is my first bout at a Korean restaurant and this place easily exceeded my expectations by a long shot. I visited on an early Friday afternoon and there was not a ton of people inside, much how I like it since that means immediate seating and less noise overall. The menu, for some reason is on these letter sized papers attached to a clipboard. I personally don't mind this at all, but others who are nitpicky may see this and immediately think poorly of the restaurant's quality, but I can assure you, the quality is top notch. Prices are pretty reasonable for most items on the menu and serving sizes are fairly big. I ended up ordering the Oh-Sam (the only thing on the menu with a fairly high price) and the shrimp fried rice. The Oh-Sam, which is fried calamari and pork belly with vegetables, arrived steaming hot on one of those cast iron-like plates where the food continues to sizzle and cook in front of you. It's mostly for show, but the only drawback is the food is HOT, and stays too hot for a while. The fried rice was served the same way. Both were absolutely delicious and outstanding. We complimented the food with a bottle of Sake, which was also amazing. Overall I can easily recommend this place. It's so delicious and so fairly priced.
(Translated by Google) I loved  (Original) Me encantó
Very good food, nice and friendly service.

Came here a couple days ago with some coworkers for lunch.  Lunch specials are decently priced. Interior has a nice vibe. Servers were polite and friendly.  I ordered the spicy soba noodles with broiled salmon. Delicious. A lil heavy on the sauce but still good. My coworkers had kimchi fried rice with jayuk (pork), bulgogi (Beef) and chicken wings. I tried some of their kimchi fried rice and that was definitely very flavorful. Everyone enjoyed their meals. I would definitely try this place again, maybe for dinner next time to see what the crowd/service is like.
We ordered dinner and they never brought it to our table. That said, I can’t weigh in if their food is good or not, just that we waited 90 minutes and never received our meal.

I was thinking about going to the German beer garden across the street but I accidentally stepped on their happy hour sign outside. "I am sorry". $6 for cocktial and $5 beer and a few other I can't resist but ends at 7pm and it's only 6:55pm.  On a Friday night, the place is not super packed. I can easily get a booth table enough for 4 or more. This spot ended up as a perfect date spot. With the correct ambiance and deal on drinks, we had a great time. Beside not having to yell at each other and overhearing someone else conversation, the waiters are so nice.  Food is delicious. We just got some tapas including their wing, kimchi pancake and some pork belly. Their Seoul mule is strong and huge which is well worth the $11 or $6 happy hour special. It's equal to two drink size tbh. The hot toddy is decent but I would go for something else.  Wing is pretty good. I think they need to be marinated a bit more as the flavor isn't all the way into the meat. The kimchi pancake is a bit sad due to the size and it's not midtown quality. They need some more work or a better recipe. This place has potential but need more work on their food of course. The bar is a good deal and drinks are on point. The noodle we had come in a sizzling hot plate but it ends up burned at the bottom. Good show but not ideal for eating.  Service is 100 %. Everyone is super nice.
Very good interior. Their cooking of the salmon is perfect!
Solid food.
Good food but nothing exciting. A lot of rice and not many veggies. The restaurant was busy yet still quiet on a Friday night.
Great traditional Korean dishes meet some fun fusion creations like bulgogi nachos and kimchee fries. Great bang for the buck and the staff is attentive but never overbearing.
The food was really good and such a cute place.  Only complaint is the bathroom was not pleasant. Door didnt lock and it was dirty and theres barely any toilet paper.
Good food & drinks!
Amazing Korean restaurant in Brooklyn

Trying to find decent Korean food away from K-Town 34th area, in the Brooklyn area, and this one was OK. The Banchan (small starter dishes) typically given to start off meals was the smallest amount I've ever seen with two tiny bowls of Kimchi. You get like 6 or 7 in Manhattan.  - The Pajun (scallion pancake) was nice. - JapChae was decent, but definitely better at other places. - The Sundubu soup was good flavor, but the meat was chewy - The fried Steak and Eggs cooked Dolsot style was the best dish. The crispy rice was flavored exceptionally well. The meat had the same issue being soft and chewy, but flavored well. Had me wonder meat quality to be this chewy  The big kicker was the spotty service. It IS very slow. We thought they were forgot our order at one point as the couple seated right before us were able to eat and receive their bill before we got our first dish. We waited almost 40min for the first order to arrive (the appetizer scallion pancake) during a lunch that was not busy at all around 1:10pm on a Sunday. They also gave us a wrong dish during this time.

Nice Korean restaurant in downtown Brooklyn. Ambience in the restaurant is warm and welcoming. Staffers are professional and food is great. Ssam restaurant is a must visit for the best Korean food experience. I'll be back again.

Food is good but don't ever get delivery. They use some retarded system with independent drivers, so when you call to check on the order, they just go "I don't know the delivery guy isn't here, " "there's no delivery guys, but your food is ready. "

Cool chill spot with amazing wings!!!

Mike took excellent care of my dear friend and I! They've got great happy hour specials, huge portions for the price, and a really sweet waitstaff. On top of that, the food was excellent and well presented. I would definitely recommend this spot to any foodie in need of ramen, cocktails, and warm vibes.
Great food!  Have been twice as I live in the area and will be returning.  Atmosphere is average.
Great service they came to check on us every now and again but not bothersome like some restaurants do. Place was nice and clean and they are actively trying to get better which is great

This place was pretty solid, we got the wings - which were amazing! They came with water kimchi (yay), we shared a pork fried rice which was the bomb!! I ordered a galbi soondubu, asked for super spicy it came mild, overall it was good- thought the kimchi was rather tropically “mango” sweet, the bibimbop was good as well- overall cute little place, it was clean- servers were attentive/ friendly. Would return/recommend.
Enjoyed my lunch here. Very flavorful.
Great food good service would go back for sure.

Would give it zero stars if possible. I showed up with a friend at 10.20PM on a Friday night. Fewer than half the tables were occupied. I asked to be seated and they said the kitchen was closed. Your posted hours are until 11PM - maybe try and follow that. I could understand if someone came 5 minutes before closing, but 40? With this level of "service", they'll be gone in 6 months.
Wonderful traditional Korean food. Large portions and great sauces. The wings are great and so are the various kimchee. Very nice ambiance too.
Great interior space, good korean food

This was my first time here, and I really enjoyed the atmosphere of the restaurant! The restaurant wasn't packed when we came in on a weekday night, so we got seated pretty quickly. We only ordered the tapas, which were decent. The soy garlic wings were lacking in flavor/sauce. The kimchi fries were very good and spicy, and the Bulgogi nachos were pretty good as well. I'd definitely like to come back and try some of the BBQ entrees.
This is an amazing place. Totally understated and just excellent. The music, the ambience, and of course the food make for a wonderful evening.

Nice food, friendly staffs and decent prices for the quality. The service was good but when we need the service, staffs are a bit neglecting. They were very focused on things that they are doing without giving a look at customers. Maybe because it was lunch time and they had to prepare for dinner time. It was very relaxed and peaceful time.
The service is very bad, it to late
Love this place. Fabulous food, great service and so generous to me and my kids. Thanks SSAM!
Great ambiance, great food. Highly recommended.
On a full scale excellent!
Good vegetarian options
Their cold noodle was really delicious and the amount very generous. The side dishes were very good too. Food came out really quickly. Want to try other dishes here next time!
We were enjoying food ❣️ very delicious and good food! I’m very love Korean food, if you too, so that’s place for you 🤗
It’s good. Not as I expected like Korean BBQ place in Korea town, but it’s decent place. A bit expensive I think...
Tasty food. The space is also great for big groups which is how I like to enjoy Korean Food! Service was a little slow, had to get a replacement spoon because the one they had was not clean. Yikes!
Really good food and the service was also good. It was a nice discovery

Okay , food service for lunch.  Chill some good bites can cure an itch to trek to Ktown.
Perfect portions. Simple menu. Not usually a long wait.

Food was delicious. A couple friends and I snuck inside to escape the rain and have lunch. It was one of those perfect moments when you've stumbled into a gem. Was super mellow, not busy, cozy wooden interior, and delicious food. Everything we ordered was excellent. My favorite, the spicy tofu stew.

Had spicy seafood Ramen which was super satisfying.  My daughter had kimchi fried rice and chicken wings which she said was perfect.  The spice of the ramen  was perfect.   Smooth and went down easy. Service was gracious and professional. Definitely coming back.

You can slap lipstick on a pig, but it would still be a pig. To say that the food is authentic is laughable at best. Poor food, poor service and offensive music. Cannot imagine ever returning or inviting anyone I call a friend to visit. The worse Korean food I've ever tasted (it was so sub standard that we returned the food and refused to pay and left)

Food is delicious, but literally the worst service I’ve ever had at a restaurant in all my years of living in New York. I’ve never written an online review, but need to warn people after my THIRD awful experience here. I have dined in twice and it has taken a half hour to even get a waiter to the table. Literally had to go and ask for the bill both times. The staff here have no business working in food service - inattentive and zero concern for their customers. Thought it would be better to order the food in and avoid the inexcusably bad service - wrong. Order was delayed twice by over an hour. No one would pick up at the restaurant after eleven calls and eventually had to get seamless to settle the issue for us. Turns out they are on Seamless but don’t have any delivery drivers?!?!? Incredible food, but it’s not like you’ll get it. And in a year they will wonder why they are out of business. Would not recommend - our last time EVER here. ABSOLUTELY TERRIBLE.
Very good place
Delicious food. Weak drinks.
I really enjoyed the chicken wings and the bi-bim-bap.  Will come back again.
Food was great! Service was understaffed so we had to ask for things throughout dinner more frequently than expected
Love the environment.

The food here is really great. Everyone enjoyed their plate. The portions are nice and the prices are fair. The decor is really up to date with the modern Brooklyn beams and antique lights style. The staff are also very polite and attentive.
Extremely friendly and attentive staff. Food was also delicious! Highly recommend coming here for your next meal!
The dynamite chicken lived up to its name. 😀
Excellent Korean food. Order the Korean Pilsner. It's great with Kimchi fries.

Food: - Korean fried chicken was chrispy on the outside and juicy on the inside. They were fried hard so the meat was very tender. 9/10  - The fried Gyoza was very average. The meat filling didn't taste fresh. 6/10  - The beef japchae tastes like any other Korean restaurant and the taste was on point. 8/10  Price: A bit expensive for fair to good food.  What I most likely about the restaurant was the rustic look to it. It provides a calming ambience.

This was the worst experience I have ever had at a restaurant. When we walked in, they seated us quickly, but we didn't get water until 10 minutes after we asked for it. The cup of water I was given had a salty taste to it. They obviously didn't wash it properly. But worst of all, the food never came. First, we asked the waiter how long it would take, having waited 30 minutes at the time. He never returned with an answer. After being at the restaurant for almost an hour with no food and dirty cups, we decided to leave. Never returning to this place.
Truffle friessssssss  yummmmmm 🐷
It was a lovely setting and outstanding customer service! Food is tasty aswell!
Food is good but do not order for delivery. They take FOREVER to get done with the delivery orders because i guess the in house customers take priority.

Omg!!! This is the best Korean cuisine in New York. The server was a really amazing woman. I told her the food was great, and then she gave me free Ginger Ale and let me stay as long as I want because I was working with a computer. This is my first time to leave a review in my whole life, so you know how impressive this restaurant is.

This place is incredible. Best interior decorating in the neighborhood, fantastic apps (try the fried chicken and the quesadilla is surprisingly delicious). And cold Sapporo on tap with friendly service, what else do you want?

Service was friendly but off. Served a skunked beer to start it off, then lukewarm dumplings. Then my main dish came out about 15 minutes before my partner's, let alone the appetizer salad we'd ordered. When her dish did arrive, she'd asked for it mild but it came out fully spicy. Like the interior and the friendly people working here, but I won't be back.
Delicious! Bartender is so nice!
Exelenet seafood jjamppong ramen!!!
Great flavor. I take non alcoholic drinks, which was perfect and fresh. Long waits, but well worth it!
Food was solid but unremarkable. A bit overpriced. Not bad, but probably won't go back.
If you like spicy food, try Jeyook Tofu Kimchi!

We won't be going back there. Careless and offhand ish  service, slow food delivery (with a completely empty restaurant), they only brought water when we were almost done eating and they were impossible to flag before then as the crew was hanging out amongst themselves and did not really pay attention to us. To add insult to injury, the entree came before appetizer,  bibimbap was B minus, $14 pork belly appetizer was really not great.  One bibimbap, one dumpling appetizer, one pork belly appetizer, no drinks=$44.48 and not a pleasant time.  Avoid.
Tasty great and kind, when I find it make me supprised and happy.

Food is good, staff is friendly, however a piece of squid was attached to my Wife's chicken. For me the food was seasoned well the spicy items were very enjoyable. Staff made sure they were attentive and pleasant. The price was a bit on the upscale side and was a bit high but will come here again on occasion. Would definitely recommend this restaurant.
Amazing food and aţmosphere. Great apps and the hot bowls were top notch.
Great Korean comfort food. Very satisfying.
The food here is so good. Every time I've been here it's so tasty and well made, perfectly seasoned, great balance in flavors and textures. This is the best comfort Korean in the hood.
Good food, not fully traditional Korean food but still food, nice reclaimed wood decor.
So many things on the menu i wanted to try. Will be back. The $16 flavored shoju is a caraffe. Decent deal.
It's not a Korean food. I got a concern for discounting K-food. There was only terrible cook and unkown copycat menu. Service was also bad. I've visited on my NY trip from SEOUL. miss ..

Im not too familiar with Korean place and went there with my colleagues. Only liked the chicken wings appetizers and the rest wasn't that impressive. May be I have to go there again to try something new.
Good ramen and bibimbop dishes, but when we went the single waitress was overwhelmed. Not her fault, get her some help during busy hours.
I'm traver from S.Korea. This Deli is so Delicious ! It don't lose any premeium restrant in S.Korea I recommend to ordering Dolsot bulgogi !
Friendly staff, low prices, and great bulgogi
This might have been the best meal of my life. Amazing service. Delicious food. I look forward to returning.
Over priced, service was not that great. Just head to flushing if craving Korean food.
Main dishes were delicious but kimchi was bland and flavorless.
Great Korean food
This place is AMAZING! The best beef dumplings I've ever had and the chicken bibimbap was incredible 😍 highly recommend!
Good service and good food.will be coming back when I have a caving for korean food. It's good to know of one in Brooklyn. Small note...come hungry...Lots of food.
The menus was confused, and the service was very spotty despite the place being basically empty. They said they had a new chef, but it seems like they need a new front of the house too.

The bibimbap was very good!  The steamed dumplings were quite tasty as well.  Service was excellent and the staff was very friendly, even helping me with some Korean phrases I practiced with them.    I will visit again next time I'm in town.
Very good bi bim bap! Solid Jap chae noodles. The ban chan is not great. Short ribs were not the best, but good enough for Korean food in Brooklyn. Skip the seafood pancake.
The food was fantastic, the wait staff was super friendly, the cocktails were very well put together, and it had a nice atmosphere.
Decent place with good fried chicken. Service was fast and staff was polite!

Great ambience, great Korean food. They have a bar and offer happy hour from 4-7. They have lots of tables, even tables for large groups. Service is fast and excellent. Glad we found this Korean restaurant in Brooklyn.
Their food is bland and lacking flavor, they will deliver and not include sauce. Save time and order elsewhere...
Nice food and service!! Also I was surprised that they were playing Jazz suite by shostakovich and rachmaninoff symphony. What a great taste on music!!!

I live nearby and come by here twice now. First time we had makgeoli (rice liquor), vegetable japchae (sweet potato glass noodles), and bulgogi. The service brings six side dishes (kimchi, pickled sprouts, tofu, cucumbers, etc.) constantly, so you're always munching on something. The japchae was our favorite dish. Total was fifty bucks. Second time around, I came with 3 friends and we ordered the japchae, chicken bibimbop and kalbi (beef short ribs). Everything was fresh, hot and delicious. Total was seventy bucks.

Good bibimbap in a variety of formats here ranging from traditional to spicy pork.  The hot stone was very hot and made for excellent crisp on the rice.  The ambiance is bifurcated japanese and korean.  Service is good.  No complaints.

My wife and I love Korean food and we had a fantastic meal here, the best Korean we have had in NYC so far. We shared the Kalbi stone BBQ and the seafood pancake, both were excellent and the service was outstanding. We will definitely be back.
Loved the bibimbap here... Really hot and spicy!!! Loved the service.. Definitely going back for sure!
